This subsection describes the analysis of the data.

\section{Results}
Here the results are presented.

\section{Conclusion}
This section contains the concluding remarks.

\end{document}
```

When you compile this LaTeX document, the `\tableofcontents` command will work with the `\section` and `\subsection` commands to create an appropriately formatted table of contents. Remember that you may need to compile the document twice to get the table of contents fully updated, especially if you make any changes that would affect the numbering or titles of sections.

